/></g></g></svg>        </a>

</header>
        <!-- main content -->
        <div id="main">
                
    <div class="container article-page py-5">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col col-lg-8 pe-lg-0">
                                    <div class="article-header">
    <p class="category text-uppercase">ESET Research</p>
    <h1 class="page-headline">Scarabs colon-izing vulnerable servers</h1>    <p class="sub-title">Analysis of Spacecolon, a toolset used to deploy Scarab ransomware on vulnerable servers, and its operators, CosmicBeetle</p>
    
    <div class="article-authors d-flex flex-wrap"><div class="article-author d-flex"><a href="/en/our-experts/jakub-soucek/" title="Jakub Souƒçek"><picture><source srcset="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/tn/-x45/wls/2023/06/Soucek_Jakub_photo.jpg" media="(max-width: 768px)" /><img class="author-image me-3"  src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/tn/-x45/wls/2023/06/Soucek_Jakub_photo.jpg" alt="Jakub Souƒçek"  /></picture></a><div class="author-text"><p><a href="/en/our-experts/jakub-soucek/" title="Jakub Souƒçek"><b>Jakub Souƒçek</b></a></p></div></div></div>
    <p class="article-info mb-5">
        <span>22 Aug 2023</span>
        <span class="d-none d-lg-inline">&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;</span>
        <span class="d-inline d-lg-none">, </span>
        <span>36 min. read</span>
    </p>

    <div class="hero-image-container">
        <picture><source srcset="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/tn/-x266/wls/2023/2023-8/cosmicbeetle.jpeg" media="(max-width: 768px)" /><source srcset="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/tn/-x425/wls/2023/2023-8/cosmicbeetle.jpeg" media="(max-width: 1120px)" /><img class="hero-image"  src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/tn/-x700/wls/2023/2023-8/cosmicbeetle.jpeg" alt="Scarabs colon-izing vulnerable servers"  /></picture>    </div>
</div>
                    <div class="article-body">
    <p>In this blogpost, ESET researchers take a look at Spacecolon, a small toolset used to deploy variants of the Scarab ransomware to victims all over the world. It probably finds its way into victim organizations by its operators compromising vulnerable web servers or via brute forcing RDP credentials.</p>
<p>Several Spacecolon builds contain a lot of Turkish strings; therefore we suspect a Turkish-speaking developer. We were able to track the origins of Spacecolon back to at least May 2020 and continue to see new campaigns at the time of writing, with the latest build compiled in May 2023. Despite this tracking and our detailed analysis of Spacecolon&rsquo;s constituent tools, we cannot currently attribute its use to any known threat actor group. Therefore, we will call Spacecolon&rsquo;s operators CosmicBeetle to represent the link to &ldquo;space&rdquo; and &ldquo;scarab&rdquo;.</p>
<p>Spacecolon consists of three Delphi components &ndash; internally known as HackTool, Installer, and Service, which will be referred to as ScHackTool, ScInstaller, and ScService in this blogpost. ScHackTool is the main orchestrator component, which allows CosmicBeetle to deploy the other two. ScInstaller is a small component with a single purpose: to install ScService. ScService acts as a backdoor, allowing CosmicBeetle to execute custom commands, download and execute payloads, and retrieve system information from compromised machines.</p>
<p>Besides these three components, Spacecolon&rsquo;s operators rely heavily on a large variety of third-party tools, both legitimate and malicious, that Spacecolon makes available on demand.</p>
<p>While preparing this report for publication, we observed a new ransomware family being developed, with samples being uploaded to VirusTotal from Turkey. We believe with high confidence that it is written by the same developer as Spacecolon; therefore we&rsquo;ll refer to it as ScRansom. Our attribution is based on similar Turkish strings in the code, usage of the IPWorks library, and the overall GUI similarity. ScRansom attempts to encrypt all hard, removable and remote drives using the AES-128 algorithm with a key generated from a hardcoded string. We have not observed ScRansom being deployed in the wild at the time of writing and we believe it is still in the development stage. The latest variant uploaded to VirusTotal is bundled inside an MSI installer, together with a small utility to delete Shadow Copies.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Key points of this blogpost:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>CosmicBeetle operators probably compromise web servers vulnerable to the ZeroLogon vulnerability or those whose RDP credentials they are able to brute force.</li>
<li>Spacecolon provides, on demand, a large variety of third-party, red team tools.</li>
<li>CosmicBeetle has no clear targeting; its victims are all over the world.</li>
<li>Spacecolon can serve as a RAT and/or deploy ransomware; we have seen it delivering Scarab.</li>
<li>Spacecolon operators or developers appear to be preparing the distribution of new ransomware that we have named ScRansom.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</blockquote>
<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The name Spacecolon was assigned by Zaufana Trzecia Strona analysts, who authored the first (and to our knowledge the only other) <a href="https://zaufanatrzeciastrona.pl/post/kiedy-nawet-dobry-edr-nie-wystarcza-case-study-prawie-udanego-ataku-z-polskiej-firmy/"><em>publication</em></a> (in Polish) about the toolset. Building on top of that publication, ESET offers deeper insight into the threat. To avoid confusion, we will refer to the toolset as Spacecolon and to its operators as CosmicBeetle.</p>
<p>The attack scenario is as follows:</p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">1.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">CosmicBeetle compromises a vulnerable web server or simply brute forces its RDP credentials.</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">2.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">CosmicBeetle deploys ScHackTool.</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">3.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">Using ScHackTool, CosmicBeetle employs any of the additional third-party tools available on demand to disable security products, extract sensitive information, and gain further access.</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">4.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">If the target is deemed valuable, CosmicBeetle can deploy ScInstaller and use it to install ScService.</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">5.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">ScService provides further remote access for CosmicBeetle.</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">6.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">Finally, CosmicBeetle may choose to deploy the Scarab ransomware through ScService or manually.</span></p>
<p>In several cases, we noticed ScService being deployed through <a href="https://github.com/fortra/impacket"><em>Impacket</em></a> rather than ScInstaller, with ScHackTool not used at all. We conclude that using ScHackTool as the initial component is not the only approach Spacecolon&rsquo;s operators employ.</p>
<p>The final payload CosmicBeetle deploys is a variant of the <a href="https://malpedia.caad.fkie.fraunhofer.de/details/win.scarab_ransom"><em>Scarab ransomware</em></a>. This variant internally also deploys a ClipBanker, a type of malware that monitors the content of the clipboard and changes content that it deems is likely to be a cryptocurrency wallet address to an attacker-controlled one.</p>
<h2>Initial acces</h2>
<p>ESET telemetry suggests that some targets are compromised via RDP brute forcing &ndash; this is further supported by the additional tools, listed in Appendix A &ndash; Third-party tools used by the attacker, available to Spacecolon operators. Besides that, we assess with high confidence that CosmicBeetle abuses the CVE-2020-1472 (ZeroLogon) vulnerability, based on a custom .NET tool described in the next section.</p>
<p>With low confidence, we assess that CosmicBeetle may also be abusing a vulnerability in FortiOS for initial access. We believe so based on the vast majority of victims having devices running FortiOS in their environment and that the ScInstaller and ScService components reference the string &ldquo;Forti&rdquo; in their code. According to CISA, three FortiOS vulnerabilities were amongst the top routinely exploited vulnerabilities in 2022. Unfortunately, we have no further details on such possible vulnerability exploitation besides these artifacts.</p>
<h3>Closing the door behind you</h3>
<p>On several occasions, ESET telemetry has shown Spacecolon operators executing a custom .NET payload that we will refer to here as ScPatcher. ScPatcher is designed to do nothing malicious. On the contrary: it installs chosen Windows Updates. The list of updates installed is illustrated in Table 1 and the corresponding code part of ScPatcher in Figure 1.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Table 1. List of Windows Updates installed by ScPatcher</em></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Windows 10</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Windows Server 2019</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 155.25pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt;" width="207">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">No clear CVE connection.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 1. Part of ScPatcher code listing the selected Windows updates" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-01-updaterurls.png" alt="Figure_01_UpdaterUrls" width="" height="" />
<figcaption>
<p class="MsoCaption"><a name="_Ref140503954"></a><em><span lang="EN-US">Figure </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140503954;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">1</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. Part of ScPatcher code listing the selected Windows updates</span></em></p>
</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>ScPatcher also contains two functions designed to drop and execute:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">update.bat</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">, a small BAT script to alter Windows Automatic Updates settings, and</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">up.vbs</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">, an almost identical copy of an <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/windows/desktop/aa387102(v=vs.85)"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;">official MSDN example</em></a> script to download and install Windows Updates with the slight change of not accepting user input, but rather allowing the updates to proceed automatically and silently.</span></p>
<p>While these two functions are not referenced anywhere in the code, ESET telemetry shows Spacecolon operators executing both scripts directly through Impacket. The functions are illustrated in Figure 2 and Figure 3.</p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 2. ScPatcher code responsible for dropping and executing a BAT script to alter Automatic Windows Update settings" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-02-updatebat.png" alt="Figure_02_UpdateBat" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><a name="_Ref140504293"></a><em>Figure 2. ScPatcher code responsible for dropping and executing a BAT script to alter Automatic Windows Update settings</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 3. ScPatcher code responsible for dropping and executing a VBScript to download and install Windows Updates" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-03-updatevbs.png" alt="Figure_03_UpdateVbs" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 3. ScPatcher code responsible for dropping and executing a VBScript to download and install Windows Updates</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<h2>Victimology</h2>
<p>We have not observed any pattern in Spacecolon victims besides them being vulnerable to the initial access methods employed by CosmicBeetle. Figure 4 illustrates the Spacecolon incidents identified by ESET telemetry.</p>
<figure class="image"><img title="" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/figure-05-ransommessage01.png" alt="Figure_05_RansomMessage01" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 4. Distribution of Spacecolon victims</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<p>We have not found any pattern in the targets&rsquo; area of focus or size either. To name a few, we have observed Spacecolon at a hospital and a tourist resort in Thailand, an insurance company in Israel, a local governmental institution in Poland, an entertainment provider in Brazil, an environmental company in Turkey, and a school in Mexico.</p>
<h2>Technical analysis</h2>
<p>We first take a brief look at the ransomware variant Spacecolon deploys and then proceed with the analysis of Spacecolon components themselves.</p>
<h3>Scarab ransomware</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.malwarebytes.com/blog/news/2018/01/scarab-ransomware-new-variant-changes-tactics"><em>Scarab</em></a> is Delphi-written ransomware. It contains notable code overlaps with the <a href="https://www.mcafee.com/blogs/other-blogs/mcafee-labs/buran-ransomware-the-evolution-of-vegalocker/"><em>Buran</em></a> and <a href="https://malpedia.caad.fkie.fraunhofer.de/details/win.vegalocker"><em>VegaLocker</em></a> families. It relies on an embedded configuration whose format is almost identical to that of the <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa22-223a"><em>Zeppelin</em></a> ransomware. That configuration determines, among other things, the file extension for encrypted files, filenames, list of file extensions of files to encrypt, and the ransom message.</p>
<p>The vast majority of Scarab builds we have encountered drop and execute an embedded Delphi-written ClipBanker that monitors the clipboard content and replaces any string resembling a cryptocurrency wallet with an attacker-controlled one, specifically one of the following:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">1HtkNb73kvUTz4KcHzztasbZVonWTYRfVx</span></span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">qprva3agrhx87rmmp5wtn805jp7lmncycu3gttmuxe</span></span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">0x7116dd46e5a6c661c47a6c68acd5391a4c6ba525</span></span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">XxDSKuWSBsWFxdJcge8xokrtzz8joCkUHF</span></span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;</span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">4BrL51JCc9NGQ71kWhnYoDRffsDZy7m1HUU7MRU4nUMXAHNFBEJhkTZV9HdaL4gfuNBxLPc3BeMkLGaPbF5vWtANQnt2yEaJRD7Km8Pnph</span></span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">t1RKhXcyj8Uiku95SpzZmMCfTiKo4iHHmnD</span></span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">We were able to conclusively link Spacecolon with at least two Scarab builds utilizing </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">.flycrypt</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">.restoreserver</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> extensions for encrypted files &ndash; CosmicBeetle attempted to execute these builds on machines that had been compromised by Spacecolon shortly beforehand. Both builds follow the same file-naming patterns &ndash; the ransomware runs as </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">%APPDATA%\osk.exe</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and the embedded ClipBanker as </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">%APPDATA%\winupas.exe</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. This naming holds special importance for Spacecolon, as ScHackTool expects two such named processes to be running. Supposing this naming pattern is closely tied to Spacecolon, more than 50% of Scarab configurations shown by ESET telemetry may be related to Spacecolon. The ransom messages for the two conclusively linked samples are illustrated in </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">5</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">6</span></span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/figure-5.png" alt="Figure 5" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 5. Scarab ransom message for the .flycrypt variant</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 6. Scarab ransom message for the .restoreserver variant" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-06-ransommessage02.png" alt="Figure_06_RansomMessage02" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 6. Scarab ransom message for the .restoreserver variant</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<h3 class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">ScHackTool</span></h3>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">ScHackTool is the main Spacecolon component used by its operators. It relies heavily on its GUI and the active participation of its operators; it allows them to orchestrate the attack, downloading and executing additional tools to the compromised machine on demand as they see fit.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">From here on, we will refer to multiple GUI components in the same way as they are defined by the Delphi programming language &ndash; </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Labels</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">TextBoxes</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">GroupBoxes</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, etc.</span></span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">ScHackTool employs a neat anti-emulation trick. When executed, a fake error message pops up (see </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">7</span></span><span lang="EN-US">). If the &ldquo;OK&rdquo; button is clicked, ScHackTool terminates. One needs to double-click on the &ldquo;g&rdquo; in the word &ldquo;reinstalling&rdquo; (highlighted in red) to actually display the main window.</span></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 7. Fake error message displayed when ScHackTool is executed" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-07-smokescreen.png" alt="Figure_07_Smokescreen" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 7. Fake error message displayed when ScHackTool is executed</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Before the main window is displayed, ScHackTool obtains a text file, </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">list.txt</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, from its C&amp;C server. This file defines what additional tools are available, their associated names, and URLs from which to download them. An example of such a file is shown in </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">8</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. All Spacecolon components, including ScHackTool, use the <a href="https://cdn.nsoftware.com/help/IPH/dlp/"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;">IPWorks</em></a> library for network communication.</span></span></p>
<pre class="language-markup"><code>CAT|TOOLS

<blockquote>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US"><em style="color: #5f6971; font-size: 15px; text-align: center;">Figure 8. An example of the list.txt file that ScHackTool uses to set up additional tools</em></span></p>
</blockquote>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Before explaining the process of parsing this file, let us briefly introduce ScHackTool&rsquo;s GUI. It consists of three main tabs (</span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Download</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Tools</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">MIMI Dump</span></span><span lang="EN-US">) and a bottom panel shared among all three of them. Since the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Download</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> tab is populated by the result of the parsing process, let&rsquo;s introduce it first alongside the parsing logic.</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<h4><a name="_Ref141466542"></a><span lang="EN-US">Download </span><span lang="EN-US">tab</span></h4>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">This tab is populated by buttons that give the operators the ability to download and execute additional tools. All these tools are available as password-protected ZIP archives (password: </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">ab1q2w3e!</span></span><span lang="EN-US">). All of them are downloaded to </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">./zip/&lt;ARCHIVE_NAME&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and extracted into </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">./&lt;ARCHIVE_NAME_WITHOUT_ZIP&gt;/</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. The downloaded archives are not removed by ScHackTool.</span></span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">What additional tools are available is defined by the aforementioned </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">list.txt</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> file. The parsing of this file is fairly straightforward. It is read line by line. If a line looks like </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">CAT|&lt;NAME&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> (probably short for &ldquo;Category&rdquo;), then a new </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">GroupBox</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> named </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">&lt;NAME&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> is created and all following entries are associated with it. Similarly, if a line looks like </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">SUB|&lt;NAME&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> (likely short for &ldquo;Subcategory&rdquo;), then a new horizontal </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Label</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> named </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">&lt;NAME&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> is added to the current category.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">All other lines are considered to be actual entries. The line is split by </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US">#</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> into two or three items:</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpFirst" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">1.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">the tool name,</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">2.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">the URL used to retrieve the tool, and</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpLast" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">3.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">an optional suffix.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">For every entry, a button titled as the tool name is created. Additionally, if the optional suffix is </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US">a <span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">folder</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, an additional button titled </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">AC</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> is created; this button simply opens Windows Explorer at the tool&rsquo;s extracted location.</span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">If the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">list.txt</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> file is not available, the malware quits. Additionally, if Spacecolon operators request a tool that is defined in </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">list.txt</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, but is not available on the associated URL, the ScHackTool process gets stuck and stops responding.</span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">As you can see in </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">9</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, one or two buttons are created for each tool. </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">TOOLS</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">PRIV</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">RAAG</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Others</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> (highlighted in red) represent the categories, and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Sniffer</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Exploit</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> (highlighted in blue) are the subcategories. A list of all the available additional tools alongside their descriptions are listed in </span><span class="Cross-reference"><span lang="EN-US">Appendix A &ndash; Third-party tools used by the attacker</span></span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 9. The Download tab listing additional tools available to download from the C&amp;C server" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-09-availabletools.png" alt="Figure_09_AvailableTools" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 9. The Download tab listing additional tools available to download from the C&amp;C server</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<h4><span lang="EN-US">Tools tab</span></h4>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">One might be keen to think that this is the main tab, but it in fact is not. Surprisingly, most of the buttons do nothing (their associated </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">OnClick</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> functions are empty). Historically, we know these buttons did work, but over time, their functionality has been removed. We provide an overview of the no-longer-functioning buttons later in the blogpost. </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">10</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> illustrates the GUI and </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">2</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> summarizes the functionality of working buttons.</span></span></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 10. Tools tab of ScHackTool" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-10-toolstab.png" alt="Figure_10_ToolsTab" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 10. Tools tab of ScHackTool</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><em><a name="_Ref140844649"></a><span lang="EN-US">Table </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140844649;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">2</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. List of functional buttons in the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US">Tools</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> tab</span></em></p>

<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: -1; mso-yfti-firstrow: yes; mso-yfti-lastfirstrow: yes; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #A6A6A6 1.5pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background2; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 166; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #A6A6A6 1.5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 5;"><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Button</span></strong></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #A6A6A6 1.5pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background2; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 166; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #A6A6A6 1.5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 1;"><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Comment</span></strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 0; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Keyboard EN</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Change the user language settings. This is done by executing a PowerShell script (</span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">task.ps1</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">) through a BAT script (</span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">a.bat</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">). The specific PowerShell commands executed are:</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">$LanguageList = Get-WinUserLanguageList</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">$LanguageList.Add("en-US")</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Set-WinUserLanguageList $LanguageList -force</span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 1; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Kill OSK</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Execute </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">taskkill.exe /f /im osk.exe</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">. As mentioned earlier, this is the filename under which the Scarab ransomware is executed. </span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 2; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Winup</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Execute </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">taskkill.exe /f /im winupas.exe</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">. As mentioned earlier, this is the filename under which the ClipBanker (associated with the Scarab ransomware) is executed.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 3; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Cobian UI Pass</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Execute <a href="https://www.cobiansoft.com/"><span style="color: #424d56; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;">Cobian UI Pass</span></a>, a freeware backup tool, while removing its configuration first. Note that this tool is not downloaded by Spacecolon. The process consists of just these two steps:</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Delete </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">C:\Program Files (x86)\Cobian Backup 11\Settings\cbEngine.ini</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Execute </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">C:\Program Files (x86)\Cobian Backup 11\cbInterface.exe</span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 4; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Add</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Add a new account with administrative rights. Username and password are specified in the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">TextBoxes</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> to the left (highlighted in red).</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 5; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">PW GEN</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Generate a random alphanumeric string in the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">TextBox</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> to the left (length is specified in the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">TextBox</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> under it). Highlighted in green.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 6; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Dec</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Decrypt a hardcoded string and display it in the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">TextBox</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> labeled </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Str</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">. Highlighted in purple.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Note: The </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Enc</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> button does nothing.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Earlier we stated that the deployed Scarab ransomware and its associated ClipBanker are named </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">osk.exe</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">winupas.exe</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. As is obvious from </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">2</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, the two associated buttons can be used to terminate those processes.</span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The area highlighted in pink is filled in when ScHackTool launches. However, no actual machine information is retrieved; Spacecolon operators need to fill it in manually.</span></p>
<h4><span lang="EN-US">MIMI Dump tab</span></h4>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The functionality in this tab used to be part of the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Tools</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> tab, but was eventually moved to a separate tab. Once again, some of the buttons do not work. The UI is illustrated in </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">11</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, and </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">3</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> summarizes the functionality of the working buttons.</span></span></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 11. MIMI Dump tab of the ScHackTool" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-11-mimidumptab.png" alt="Figure_11_MimiDumpTab" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 11. MIMI Dump tab of the ScHackTool</em></figcaption>
</figure>

<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #A6A6A6 1.5pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background2; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 166; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #A6A6A6 1.5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 5;"><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Button</span></strong></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 395.0pt; border-top: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #A6A6A6 1.5pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background2; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 166; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #A6A6A6 1.5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="527">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 1;"><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Comment</span></strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 0; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Send</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 395.0pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="527">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Upload a file to the C&amp;C server.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">The steps are:</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpFirst" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">1.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Take the file from the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">TextBox</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> labeled </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Dump.</span></span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">2.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Create a copy and name it </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">lsa.file</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> (or </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">lsass.dmp</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> in older builds).</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">3.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Store this file into </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">dump.zip</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">.</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">4.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Upload </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">dump.zip</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> to the C&amp;C server.</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">5.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Open a file named </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">lastlog.txt</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> in Notepad.</span></p>
<p class="Bullets2" style="mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; position: relative; top: 3.0pt; mso-text-raise: -3.0pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&deg;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">The file is probably created by the underlying IPWorks library that implements the transfer.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 1; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Parse</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 395.0pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="527">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Download two text files from the C&amp;C server and paste one into the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">User</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> and the other into the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Pass</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">TextArea</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 2; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Downloaded</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 395.0pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="527">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Show a </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">MessageBox</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> with the list of tools already downloaded to the machine (see </span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">12</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">).</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 12. The MessageBox that lists all the tools already available on the compromised system when the Downloaded button is clicked" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-12-installedtoolsmsgbox.png" alt="Figure_12_InstalledToolsMsgBox" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 12. The MessageBox that lists all the tools already available on the compromised system when the Downloaded button is clicked</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The name of this tab would suggest that it is closely tied to the infamous password and credential-extracting tool Mimikatz, but in fact it is not. While the file </span>that is sent back to the Spacecolon C&amp;C <span lang="EN-US">is named to suggest a </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">lsass.exe</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> dump, the file must be created manually by the operators, and it can be any arbitrary file. Similarly, the downloaded usernames and passwords are not utilized in any way unless copied by the operators.</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">However, Mimikatz <em>is</em> part of the set of additional tools provided by Spacecolon (see </span><span class="Cross-reference"><span lang="EN-US">Appendix A &ndash; Third-party tools used by the attacker</span></span><span lang="EN-US">).</span></p>
<h4><span lang="EN-US">Bottom panel</span></h4>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The bottom panel, shared among all three tabs, allows CosmicBeetle to schedule a system restart, remove Spacecolon from the system, and access <a href="https://portableapps.com/"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;">PortableApps</em></a>, one of the additional tools. The </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Download</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Zip</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> progress bars correspond to the download and tool archive extraction progress, respectively. An overview of the buttons&rsquo; functionality is provided in </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">4</span></span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><em><a name="_Ref140846058"></a><span lang="EN-US">Table </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140846058;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">4</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. List of the buttons in the bottom panel shared between the three tabs, and their functionalities</span></em></p>

<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">taskkill.exe /f /im PortableAppsPlatform.exe</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">taskkill.exe /f /im nl.exe</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">taskkill.exe /f /im advanced_port-scanner.exe</span></span></p>

<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">DELETE</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 395.0pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="527">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Remove all files and folders recursively from the application&rsquo;s location. Also execute </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">taskkill.exe /f /im PortableAppsPlatform.exe</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 3; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Folder</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 395.0pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="527">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Open Windows&rsquo; File Explorer in the application&rsquo;s location.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 4; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">R</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 395.0pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="527">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Schedule a system restart.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 5; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.65pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="94">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">A</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 395.0pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="527">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Abort scheduled system restart.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<h4><span lang="EN-US">String encryption</span></h4>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">ScHackTool encrypts strings with a simple algorithm &ndash; we provide the decryption routine implemented in Python in </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">13</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. Not all of the strings are encrypted, though with newer builds, the number of protected strings increases.</span></p>
<pre class="language-python"><code>def decrypt_string(s: str, key: str) -&gt; str:
    dec = ""
    for b in bytearray.fromhex(s):
        dec += chr(b ^ (key &gt;&gt; 8))
        key = (0xD201 * (b + key) + 0x7F6A) &amp; 0xFFFF
 
    return dec
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="text-align: center;"><a name="_Ref140846231"></a><span lang="EN-US">Figure </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140846231;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">13</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. String decryption routine for SCHackTool strings</span></p>
</blockquote>
<h4><span lang="EN-US">ScHackTool buttons &ndash; a trip back in time</span></h4>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">ScHackTool is definitely the component that has undergone the most changes. The oldest build we were able to find is from 2020 and uses <a href="https://cdn.nsoftware.com/help/CS1/dlp/Dropbox.htm"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;">TicsDropbox</em></a> for communication with its C&amp;C server. At that time, instead of the fake error message, a password protection mechanism (see </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">14</span></span><span lang="EN-US">) was in place (password: </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">dd1q2w3e</span></span><span lang="EN-US">).</span></span></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 14. Password-protection window in an old variant of ScHackTool" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-14-loginui.png" alt="Figure_14_LoginUI" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 14. Password-protection window in an old variant of ScHackTool</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Weirdly, with each new version, some buttons stopped working (their code was completely removed). By being able to peek into these older builds, we can learn the functionality of the no-longer-functional buttons, which are listed in </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">5</span></span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><em><a name="_Ref140859394"></a><span lang="EN-US">Table </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140859394;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">5</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. A list of button functionalities based on analysis of older builds</span></em></p>
