</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Used to drop and execute scripts to delete Shadow Copies, delete Windows Event Logs, and modify boot options. These scripts are now part of the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">BAT</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> tool listed in </span><span class="Cross-reference"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Appendix A &ndash; Third-party <a name="_Hlt143270835"></a>tools used by the attacker</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">.</span></p>

<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 5; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.9pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="95">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Recent Files</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Used to drop and execute a small script that removes all files located at:</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">%APPDATA%\Microsoft\Windows\Recent\AutomaticDestinations\*</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">%APPDATA%\Microsoft\Windows\Recent\CustomDestinations\*</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">%APPDATA%\Microsoft\Windows\Recent\*</span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 6; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.9pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="95">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Credssp</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Used to modify the settings of the <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/secauthn/credential-security-support-provider"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;"><span style="mso-fareast-language: EN-US;">Credential </span>Security Support Provider (CredSSP)</em></a> by issuing the following command (probably to overcome potential RDP connection issues):</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">reg add &ldquo;HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\<br />Policies\System\CredSSP\Parameters" /f /v AllowEncryptionOracle /t REG_DWORD /d 2</span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 7; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.9pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="95">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Button5</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Encrypt a hardcoded URL and paste it to the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Edit1</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">TextBox</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">. This button is probably a predecessor of the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Enc</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Dec</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> buttons. Strangely, the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Dec</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> button currently works while </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Enc</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> does not.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 8; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 70.9pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="95">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">Button20</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 411.1pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="548">
<p class="Numbering1" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Close the fake error message displayed on startup. This behavior is very strange, as at the point when the button could be clicked, the error message no longer exists. Indeed, clicking this button causes ScHackTool to crash.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<h3><a name="_Toc143276482"></a><span lang="EN-US">ScInstaller</span></h3>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">ScInstaller is a very small Delphi tool designed to do a single task: install ScService. ScService is stored in ScInstaller&rsquo;s </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">.rsrc</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> section, encrypted with the AES algorithm using a key derived from the password </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">TFormDropbox.btnUploadClick</span></span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">ScInstaller is part of the additional tools the attacker may or may not utilize, specifically the one named </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">AGENT</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> (see </span><span class="Cross-reference"><span lang="EN-US">Appendix A &ndash; Third-party tools used by the attacker</span></span><span lang="EN-US">). Despite the newest observed build coming from 2021, that build is still part of the toolset at the time of writing. However, we have observed ScService installed manually through Impacket, and, while we have observed new builds of ScService, we have seen no new builds of ScInstaller. This may suggest ScInstaller is no longer actively used.</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The earlier variants of ScInstaller simply installed and ran ScService on execution. The more recent variants come with a GUI (see </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">15</span></span><span lang="EN-US">). ScService is installed only if the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Install</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> button is clicked.</span></span></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 15. ScInstaller GUI" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-15-installerui.png" alt="Figure_15_InstallerUI" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 15. ScInstaller GUI</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">They also come with a few additional features. The </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Check</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> button at the bottom verifies whether ScService is installed and retrieves the service status. The </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Check</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> button at the top left is used to check connectivity to four hardcoded C&amp;C servers (no actual data is exchanged). ScInstaller also drops its own TLS certificate in a PFX file named </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">cert.pfx</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> or </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">cdn.pfx</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and protected by the password </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">dd1q2w3e</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. This certificate is used when connecting to the C&amp;C server(s).</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">TextBoxes</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> labeled </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Forti IP</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Not</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> are used to create a small INI file with two entries &ndash; </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Data</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Note</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, filled by those two values, respectively. This INI file is merely used by CosmicBeetle to store custom notes about the victim. It plays a minor role in C&amp;C communication described in the next section.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<h3><a name="_Toc143276483"></a><span lang="EN-US">ScService</span></h3>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">In March 2023, possibly as the result of the Zaufana Trzecia Strona</span><span class="cf01"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 9.0pt;"> </span></span><span lang="EN-US">analysis published in early February 2023, ScService underwent a notable development change. Let&rsquo;s first look at its earlier variant and then discuss the 2023 changes.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">ScService, as the name suggests, is a component run as a Windows service and acts as a simple backdoor. The service parameters are shown in </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">6</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. The service description was taken from the official legitimate Windows <a href="https://batcmd.com/windows/10/services/sensrsvc/"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;">Sensor Monitoring Service</em></a>.</span></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><em><a name="_Ref140847567"></a><span lang="EN-US">Table </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140847567;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">6</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. ScService parameters</span></em></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><p><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>

<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 2; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 84.8pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="113">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Description</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 397.15pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="530">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Monitors various sensors in order to expose data and adapt to system and user state. If this service is stopped or disabled, the display brightness will not adapt to lighting conditions. Stopping this service may affect other system functionality and features as well.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">As with ScInstaller, ScService also drops a custom TLS certificate, identical to the one used by ScInstaller. If the INI file (created by ScInstaller) is not present, one with empty values is created.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Once launched, ScService creates three timers, one each that:</span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpFirst" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">1.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">sends a </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">KEEP</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> message to the C&amp;C server every 10 seconds,</span></span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpMiddle" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-font-family: 'Courier New'; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">2.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';"> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">flushes the DNS cache every five hours by executing </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">ipconfig /flushdns</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, and</span></span></p>
<p class="Numbering1CxSpLast" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">3.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">connects to the C&amp;C server every five minutes.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">16</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> demonstrates the use of the custom certificate when establishing a connection to the C&amp;C server. ScService uses multiple C&amp;C servers, all hardcoded and encrypted in the binary.</span></p>
<figure class="image"><img title="Figure 16. Use of custom certificate upon connecting to the C&amp;C server" src="https://web-assets.esetstatic.com/wls/2023/2023-8/spacecolon/figure-16-certificateusage.png" alt="Figure_16_CertificateUsage" width="" height="" />
<figcaption><em>Figure 16. Use of custom certificate upon connecting to the C&amp;C server</em></figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Aside from establishing a TLS connection, ScService communicates with the C&amp;C server via TCP on port 443. The protocol is very straightforward; no additional encryption is employed. Once ScService receives data, it scans the data for known command names and executes any such command, optionally sending back a response. ScService recognizes the six commands shown in </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">7</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. Command name and its parameters are delimited by </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US">#</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. In short, ScService can execute arbitrary commands and executables, open and close an SSH tunnel, obtain machine info, and update the INI file.</span></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><em><a name="_Ref140848439"></a><span lang="EN-US">Table </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140848439;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">7</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. TCP/IP commands capability</span></em></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><p><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>

<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">DETAILS#GET</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 127.55pt; border: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">RESULT#DETAILS#&lt;OS&gt;#&lt;UPTIME&gt;#&lt;REMOTE_HOST&gt;#&lt;INI_CONTENT&gt;</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 227.05pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="303">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Upload compromised machine info:</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;OS&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> = OS name</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;UPTIME&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> = Uptime (retrieved via the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">GetTickCount</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> API)</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;REMOTE_HOST&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> = The C&amp;C server it is connected to</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;INI_CONTENT&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> = Content of the INI file</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 2; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 127.35pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">SETNOTE#&lt;NOTE&gt;</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 127.55pt; border: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">N/A</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 227.05pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="303">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Set </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;NOTE&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> as the content of the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Note</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> field in the INI file.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 3; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 127.35pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="FR-CA" style="mso-ansi-language: FR-CA; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">TUNNEL#&lt;HOST&gt;#&lt;PORT&gt;#&lt;USER&gt;#&lt;PWD&gt;#&lt;SRC_PORT&gt;#&lt;DST_PORT&gt;</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 127.55pt; border: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">OK : TUNNEL</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 227.05pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="303">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Opens an SSH tunnel to the compromised machine for the attacker. Connects to a destination via SSH implemented by <a href="https://docs.devart.com/sbridge/index.html?tscsshclient.htm"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;"><span style="mso-fareast-language: EN-US;">TScSSHClient</span></em></a>. Connects to </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;HOST&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> at </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;PORT&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> using username </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;USER&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> and password </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;PASS&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> and instructs </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;HOST&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> to listen on </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;SRC_PORT&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> and forward the communication. It seems that </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;DST_PORT&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> is not used properly.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 4; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 127.35pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">DISCONNECT</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 127.55pt; border: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">N/A</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 227.05pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="303">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Disconnect the connection set up by the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">TUNNEL</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> command.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 5; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 127.35pt; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 132;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">DOWNEXEC#&lt;URL&gt;#&lt;FILE&gt;#&lt;FLAG&gt;</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 127.55pt; border: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="170">
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="margin-left: 0cm; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: 0cm; mso-list: none; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">N/A</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 227.05pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="303">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Download from </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;URL&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> to </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;FILE&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">. If </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;FLAG&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"> equals </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">1</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">, execute the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;FILE&gt;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<h4><span lang="EN-US">March 2023 redesign</span></h4>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">As we already hinted, ScService underwent a notable change in March 2023. First of all, the service parameters changed slightly, keeping a similar pattern (see </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">8</span></span><span lang="EN-US">).</span></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><em><a name="_Ref140848606"></a><span lang="EN-US">Table </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140848606;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">8</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. Updated ScService parameters</span></em></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><p><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Description</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 397.2pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="530">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">The Diagnostic Event System is used by the Diagnostic Policy Service to event diagnostics that need to run in a Local Service context.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The way that compromised machine info is obtained changed. ScService runs a local HTTP server on port 8347 accepting a single request &ndash; </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">/status</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. ScService then issues this request to the server. The handling of this request is simple: it retrieves machine information and returns it as the content of the HTTP response. The data is formatted in a way that it can be stored in an INI file &ndash; which is precisely what happens: ScService stores the content into its INI file. The collected information is:</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">OS</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> = operating system name</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">CN</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> = computer name</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">DO</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> = user domain</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">LIP</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> = local IP addresses</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="Italics"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-style: italic;">Many (not all) strings are now encrypted using </span></span><span lang="EN-US">the <span class="Italics"><span style="mso-bidi-font-style: italic;">AES-CBC algorithm with </span></span>a<span class="Italics"><span style="mso-bidi-font-style: italic;"> key derived from </span></span>the<span class="Italics"><span style="mso-bidi-font-style: italic;"> password </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">6e4867bb3b5fb30a9f23c696fd1ebb5b</span></span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The C&amp;C protocol changed. Interestingly, the <em>original</em> C&amp;C communication protocol remains implemented, but is only used when instructed by the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">CONNECT</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> command (see below) to communicate with a target. The new <em>main</em> C&amp;C protocol uses HTTP instead of TCP. The following HTTP headers are used:</span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">User-Agent</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> = </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:41.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/41.0</span></span></span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">UNID</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> = hexlified MD5 hash of MAC address and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">C:</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> drive serial number</span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Additionally, a </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Session</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> cookie is added with its value being the previously collected machine information stored as </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">OS</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">CN</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">DO</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">LIP</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, joined by </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US">#</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and encoded by base64.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Commands are in JSON format (see </span><span lang="EN-US">Figure <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">17 below</span></span><span lang="EN-US">).</span></p>
<pre class="language-json"><code>{
    &ldquo;Status&rdquo;: &ldquo;TASK&rdquo;,
    &ldquo;CMD&rdquo;: &ldquo;&lt;COMMAND_NAME&gt;&rdquo;,
    &ldquo;Params&rdquo;: &ldquo;&lt;COMMAND_PARAMS_STR&gt;&rdquo;,
    &ldquo;TaskID&rdquo;: &ldquo;&lt;TASK_ID&gt;&rdquo;
}
</code></pre>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>
<blockquote>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="text-align: center;"><a name="_Ref140851735"></a><span lang="EN-US">Figure </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140851735;"><span lang="EN-US">17</span></span><span lang="EN-US">. Example of JSON-formatted command</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Status</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> field is always equal to </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">TASK</span></span><span lang="EN-US">, while the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">CMD</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> and </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">Params</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> fields define the command name and parameters. Finally, the </span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">TaskID</span></span><span lang="EN-US"> value is used to send the task result, if any, to the C&amp;C server. Supported commands are listed in </span><span lang="EN-US">Table <span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">9</span></span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: center;"><em><a name="_Ref140852015"></a><span lang="EN-US">Table </span><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref140852015;"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="mso-no-proof: yes;">9</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. HTTP(S) commands capability of ScService</span></em></p>

   Name="Table Classic 1"/>

   Name="Table Classic 2"/>
  <w:LsdException Locked="false" SemiHidden="true" UnhideWhenUsed="true"
   Name="Table Classic 3"/>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">USERADD</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 6.0cm; border: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="227">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">&lt;USERNAME&gt;#&lt;PASSWORD&gt;</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 219.95pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="293">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Add a new administrator account with given username and password.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></p>
<h2><a name="_Toc143276484"></a><span lang="EN-US">Conclusion</span></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">In this blogpost, we have analyzed Spacecolon, a small Delphi toolset used to push the Scarab ransomware to vulnerable servers and its operators we call CosmicBeetle. Additionally, Spacecolon can provide backdoor access for its operators.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">CosmicBeetle doesn&rsquo;t make much effort to hide its malware and leaves plenty of artifacts on compromised systems. Little to no anti-analysis or anti-emulation techniques are implemented. ScHackTool relies heavily on its GUI, but, at the same time, contains several nonfunctional buttons. CosmicBeetle operators use ScHackTool mainly to download additional tools of choice to compromised machines and run them as they see fit.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Spacecolon has been in active use since at least 2020 and is under ongoing development. We believe the authors made a substantial effort to try to evade detection in 2023, after the Zaufana Trzecia Strona</span><span lang="EN-US"> publication came out.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">CosmicBeetle does not choose its targets; rather, it finds servers with critical security updates missing and exploits that to its advantage.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">At the time of publication, we observed a new ransomware family, which we have named ScRansom, that is very likely written by the developer of the Spacecolon components. We have not seen ScRansom being deployed in the wild as of this writing.</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p class="MsoCaption" style="break-after: avoid; text-align: left;">For any inquiries about our research published on WeLiveSecurity, please contact us at&nbsp;<a style="background-color: #f4f4f4;" href="mailto:threatintel@eset.com?utm_source=welivesecurity.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=autotagging&amp;utm_content=eset-research&amp;utm_term=en">threatintel@eset.com</a>.<br />ESET Research offers private APT intelligence reports and data feeds. For any inquiries about this service, visit the&nbsp;<a style="background-color: #f4f4f4;" href="https://www.eset.com/int/business/services/threat-intelligence/?utm_source=welivesecurity.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=wls-research&amp;utm_content=scarabs-colon-izing-vulnerable-servers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ESET Threat Intelligence</a> page.</p>
</blockquote>

<h3><span lang="EN-US">Paths where Spacecolon is usually installed</span></h3>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">%USERPROFILE%\Music\</span></span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">%ALLUSERSPROFILE%\</span></span></span></p>

<p class="Bullets1CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">support</span></span></span></p>
<p class="Bullets1CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">IIS</span></span></span></p>

<p class="Bullets1CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span class="Code"><span lang="PT-BR" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-ansi-language: PT-BR;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class="Code"><span lang="PT-BR" style="mso-ansi-language: PT-BR;"><span style="font-family: courier new, courier, monospace;">{7F57FB1B-3D23-F225-D2E8-FD6FCF7731DC}</span></span></span></p>

<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 4; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">

<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Initial Access</span></strong></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 3.0cm; border: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="113">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><a href="https://attack.mitre.org/versions/v12/techniques/T1190"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;">T1190</em></a></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 4.0cm; border: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="151">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Exploit Public-Facing Application</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 7.0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="265">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 64;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">CosmicBeetle exploited ZeroLogon, and probably other vulnerabilities, to compromise systems.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 5; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">

<td style="width: 7.0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="265">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">CosmicBeetle may deploy a large variety of tools to crack or brute force credentials for local accounts.</span></p>

<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 32; page-break-inside: avoid; height: 22.7pt;">
<td style="width: 3.0cm; border-top: none; border-left: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-left-themecolor: background1; mso-border-left-themeshade: 191; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-left-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" rowspan="4" width="113">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 68;"><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Impact</span></strong></p>

<h2><a name="_Ref138671832"></a><a name="_Toc143276491"></a><span style="mso-bookmark: _Ref138671832;"><span lang="EN-US">Appendix A &ndash; Third-party tools used by the attacker</span></span></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">The tools in the following table are ordered by name. The &ldquo;Tool name&rdquo; column corresponds to the name assigned to the tool archive by the threat actor and the &ldquo;Archive path&rdquo; column lists the relative path of the tool&rsquo;s archive on the C&amp;C server. The tools at the very end whose &ldquo;Tool name&rdquo; is set to &ldquo;N/A&rdquo; refer to tools that are present on the C&amp;C server, but not used by CosmicBeetle in any configuration known to us. Finally, some tools seem to no longer be present on the C&amp;C server, though a button to request them still exists in the ScHackTool &ndash; this is reflected by the &ldquo;Comment&rdquo; column being set to &ldquo;N/A&rdquo;.</span></p>

<p class="Bullets2CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; position: relative; top: 3.0pt; mso-text-raise: -3.0pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&deg;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">delete Shadow Copies,</span></p>

<p class="Bullets2CxSpMiddle" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; position: relative; top: 3.0pt; mso-text-raise: -3.0pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&deg;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">delete Windows Logs, and</span></p>
<p class="Bullets2CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; position: relative; top: 3.0pt; mso-text-raise: -3.0pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&deg;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">terminate several processes and services (refer to </span><span class="Cross-reference"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Appendix B &ndash; List of terminated processes and services</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">).</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1" style="mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><a href="https://www.sordum.org/9480/defender-control-v2-1/"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;"><span style="mso-fareast-language: EN-US;">Defender Control</span></em></a>, a tool to disable Windows Defender.</span></p>

<td style="width: 212.85pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A6A6A6 .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background2; mso-border-top-themeshade: 166; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="284">

<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span class="Code"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">/tools/clearev.zip</span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 212.85pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-themecolor: background1; mso-border-bottom-themeshade: 191; border-right: solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt; mso-border-right-themecolor: background1; mso-border-right-themeshade: 191; mso-border-top-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-top-themecolor: background1; mso-border-top-themeshade: 191; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; mso-border-right-alt: solid #BFBFBF .5pt; padding: .55pt 5.4pt .55pt 5.4pt; height: 22.7pt;" width="284">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">Contains:</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1" style="mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">a collection of scripts to:</span></p>
<p class="Bullets2CxSpFirst" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; position: relative; top: 3.0pt; mso-text-raise: -3.0pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&deg;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">delete Windows Event Logs, and</span></p>
<p class="Bullets2CxSpLast" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; position: relative; top: 3.0pt; mso-text-raise: -3.0pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&deg;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;">delete Shadow Backups.</span></p>
<p class="Bullets1" style="mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; mso-yfti-cnfc: 128;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0096a1; mso-themecolor: accent2; mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-language: EN-CA;"><a href="https://clearlock-2.software.informer.com/1.4/"><em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;"><span style="mso-fareast-language: EN-US;">ScreenLock</span></em></a> (also contained in the Afterwork archive).</span></p>
</td>
